This PR reclassifies silent (no stderr) non-zero exits from the `acpx` backend as `ACP_BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE` rather than the generic `ACP_TURN_FAILED`, giving users more actionable guidance (`/acp doctor`) when the backend process disappears without a structured error. Permission-denied exits (code 5) are deliberately kept as `ACP_TURN_FAILED` to preserve the existing configuration guidance.

